## toString
 `toString(int i, int radix)` `toString(int i)` `toString(int i, 10)`
```
    public static String toString(int i, int radix) {
        if (radix < Character.MIN_RADIX || radix > Character.MAX_RADIX)
            radix = 10;

        /* Use the faster version */
        if (radix == 10) {
            return toString(i);
        }
        // int 32
        char buf[] = new char[33];
        boolean negative = (i < 0);
        int charPos = 32;

        if (!negative) {
            i = -i;
        }
        // 
        while (i <= -radix) {
            buf[charPos--] = digits[-(i % radix)];
            i = i / radix;
        }
        buf[charPos] = digits[-i];

        if (negative) {
            buf[--charPos] = '-';
        }

        return new String(buf, charPos, (33 - charPos));
    }
```
**** `If the first argument is negative, the first element of the result is the ASCII minus character '-' ('\u005Cu002D'). If the first argument is not negative, no sign character appears in the result. `
```
Integer.toString(-44, 2)  // -101100
Integer.toBinaryString(-44) // 11111111111111111111111111010100
```
